This repository is **source-available**, **not open-source**.

It is published in public so that the brand it represents — Wildhaven AI
Homes — can operate, iterate, and be evaluated transparently before the
company incorporates. The build-in-public bet is to *show the thinking*,
not to *give away the work*.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## What you may do

- Read the contents of this repository.
- Quote brief, attributed excerpts (a few sentences, with a link back),
  the way you'd quote any public writing.
- Open issues and pull requests against this repository to engage with
  the brand or propose refinements. Submitted contributions are subject
  to a contributor license assignment that will be finalized when the
  company incorporates; until then, by submitting a PR you grant Kody
  Wildfeuer a perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free license to use,
  modify, and relicense your contribution as part of this repo.
- Discuss, link to, and reference this repository in your own work.

## What you may not do

- Copy, modify, redistribute, or sublicense any portion of this
  repository (in whole or in part) for any purpose, commercial or
  non-commercial.
- Operate a competing product, service, or brand that uses any
  portion of this repository's text, design, agent definitions,
  body_function code, or vision document.
- Use the names "Wildhaven", "Wildhaven AI Homes", "AI Homes",
  any associated logos, or any confusingly similar marks to identify
  any product, service, or organization. These names are claimed as
  trademarks of Kody Wildfeuer and (in the future) the Wildhaven AI
  Homes legal entity.
- Train a machine-learning model on the contents of this repository
  for the purpose of producing a competing brand-twin or a competing
  Pre-Founder twin product.
- Present any fork, copy, or derivative as being affiliated with,
  endorsed by, or originating from Wildhaven AI Homes.

## What about the platform underneath?

This repository is a **variant** of the RAPP digital-organism platform
([kody-w/RAPP](https://github.com/kody-w/RAPP)). Lineage is recorded
in [`rappid.json`](./rappid.json) and follows the variant lineage
protocol of RAPP's Constitution Article XXXIV.

The RAPP platform itself is independently licensed by its own repository.
Nothing in this LICENSE restricts what you may do with the upstream RAPP
platform — that is governed by RAPP's own license terms.

The pattern this repo demonstrates — **a Pre-Founder twin operating in
public as a RAPP variant** — is conceptual and freely reusable. You are
welcome to build your own Pre-Founder twin for your own brand. You are
not welcome to copy *this* one's content.

## Future licensing

When Wildhaven AI Homes Inc. (or successor entity) is incorporated,
this LICENSE will be superseded by the company's chosen licensing
structure. The expected shape — though not a commitment — is a split
license:

- **Code** (agents, body_functions, utilities) → a permissive
  open-source license (e.g., Apache 2.0).
- **Brand prose** (README, MANIFEST, soul, vision documents) →
  Creative Commons BY-NC-ND or equivalent.
- **Trademarks** (Wildhaven, Wildhaven AI Homes, logos) → retained
  by the company, separately enforced.

Until that incorporation moment, all rights are reserved.

## Requesting use

If you want to use anything in this repository for any purpose not
covered above — research, analysis, integration, partnership, content
licensing, fork-with-permission — please open an issue at
https://github.com/kody-w/wildhaven-ai-homes-twin/issues describing
what you want to do, and we will respond.

